author.name: Michele Bini, Ron Garret, Guy K. Kloss

dayInc.name: unit.js
dayInc.description: Simple, intuitive and flexible unit testing framework for javascript / Node.js (browser and server). Integrates awesome assertions libraries like Must.js, Should.js, Assert of Node.js, Sinon.js and other friendly features (promise, IoC, plugins, ...).

dayInc.name: noder.io
dayInc.description: A lightweight IoC container to build the core of a scalable and modular API (inspired by Angular and Pimple). No dependencies, works on Node.js and in the browser (only 2kb minified gzipped).

dayInc.name: must
dayInc.description: Testing and assertion library with friendly BDD syntax — awesome.must.be.true(). Many expressive matchers and is test runner and framework agnostic. Follows RFC 2119 with its use of MUST. Good and well tested stuff.

dayInc.name: kindof
dayInc.description: A proper typeof that works with primitives, built-in value objects and those from other execution contexts.

dayInc.name: buffertools
dayInc.description: Working with node.js buffers made easy.

dayInc.name: babel-plugin-typecheck
dayInc.description: Transforms flow type annotations into runtime type checks.

dayInc.name: map-limit
dayInc.description: async.mapLimit's functionality available as a standalone npm module

dayInc.name: roadrunner
dayInc.description: Cache require resolutions to heavily improve startup speed on subsequent loads

dayInc.name: deeper
dayInc.description: JavaScript "deep equality" / structural equality tester with Node.js flavor.

dayInc.name: only-shallow
dayInc.description: like `deeper` and `deepest`, but less strict, and with 90s flavor

dayChange.name: always-done
dayChange.description: Handle completion and errors with elegance! Support for streams, callbacks, promises, child processes, async/await and sync functions. A drop-in replacement for [async-done][] - pass 100% of its tests plus more

dayChange.name: mukla
dayChange.description: Small, parallel and fast test framework with suppport for async/await, promises, callbacks, streams and observables. Targets and works at node.js v0.10 and above.

dayChange.name: is-async-function
dayChange.description: Is function really asynchronous function? Trying to guess that based on check if [common-callback-names][] exists as function arguments names or you can pass your custom.

dayChange.name: arr-includes
dayChange.description: Return positive value if any of passed values exists in array, or optionally an index.

dayChange.name: babel-preset-node7
dayChange.description: Babel preset for Node 7.x

dayChange.name: is-child-process
dayChange.description: Checks whether a value is child process result, which in case is more specific Node.js EventEmitter. Browserify-ready.

dayChange.name: try-catch-core
dayChange.description: Low-level package to handle completion and errors of sync or asynchronous functions, using [once][] and [dezalgo][] libs. Useful for and used in higher-level libs such as [always-done][] to handle completion of anything.

dayChange.name: remark-usage
dayChange.description: Add a usage example to your README

dayChange.name: get-fn-name
dayChange.description: Get function name with strictness and correctness in mind. Also works for arrow functions and getting correct name of bounded functions. Powered by [fn-name][].

dayChange.name: is-kindof
dayChange.description: Check type of given javascript value. Support promises, generators, streams, and native types. Built on [kind-of][] lib.

dayChange.name: is-es6-generators
dayChange.description: Check whether a value is a `Generator` or `GeneratorFunction`. The `co` way, more strict checking. Always return boolean true or false, never null or undefined.

dayChange.name: kind-of-types
dayChange.description: List of all javascript types. Used and useful for checking, validation, sanitizing and testing. Like isStream, isPromise, isWeakset and etc.

dayChange.name: is-es6-generator
dayChange.description: Check that given value is Generator

dayChange.name: assert-kindof
dayChange.description: Check native type of value and throw AssertionError if not okey. Clean stack traces. Simplicity. Built on [is-kindof][].

dayChange.name: kind-of-extra
dayChange.description: Additional functionality to [kind-of][] type check utility. Support promises, generators, streams, errors.

dayChange.name: is-typeof-error
dayChange.description: Check that given value is any type of error and instanceof Error.

dayChange.name: on-stream-end
dayChange.description: Handles completion and errors of any stream - readable/writable/duplex.

dayChange.name: gluejs
dayChange.description: Build CommonJS modules for the browser via a chainable API

dayChange.name: is-node-emitter
dayChange.description: Strictly checks that given value is nodejs EventEmitter. It's easy, because his API is in frozen state.

dayChange.name: is-node-stream
dayChange.description: Strictly and correctly checks if value is a nodejs stream.

dayChange.name: common-callback-names
dayChange.description: List of common callback names - callback, cb, callback_, next, done.

dayChange.name: is-request-stream
dayChange.description: Check that given value is request stream

dayChange.name: try-catch-callback
dayChange.description: try/catch block with a callback, used in [try-catch-core][]. Use it when you don't care about asyncness so much and don't want guarantees. If you care use [try-catch-core][].

dayChange.name: test-jstransformer
dayChange.description: A CLI for testing jstransformer implementations.

dayChange.name: cept
dayChange.description: Intercept method calls
